### Fix 3: Verify the DPAH Vite proxy covers the agentic dashboard

Your DPAH React frontend (`10.5.1.58`) talks to DPAH's FastAPI backend via a Vite proxy. That works fine.

But when DPAH's sidebar calls `/api/v1/auth/handoff-token`, that goes to DPAH's backend — correct.

The redirect then sends the user to `http://10.5.1.24:5001` (agentic dashboard frontend). At that point the BROWSER is making requests directly to `10.5.1.24:5001` (agentic backend). This is where CORS matters.

Check your agentic dashboard's `vite.config.js`. It should proxy `/api` to its own backend:
```javascript
export default {
  server: {
    proxy: {
      '/api': {
        target: 'http://10.5.1.24:5001',  // update to new port
        changeOrigin: true,
      }
    }
  }
}
```

If this proxy exists and the agentic frontend is accessed via `http://10.5.1.24:5173` (or whatever port Vite runs on), then the React app talks to `/api/...` which proxies to `localhost:5001` — no CORS at all because it's same-origin. This is the cleanest setup.

