### Fix 4: Verify JWT secrets actually match

This is the most common silent failure in JWT handoff flows. The handoff token validates correctly in testing but fails in production because the secrets differ.

Run this quick check — on the DPAH server:
```cmd
python -c "import os; print('DPAH secret:', repr(os.getenv('JWT_SECRET', 'NOT SET')))"
```

On the agentic dashboard server:
```cmd
python -c "import os; print('Agentic secret:', repr(os.getenv('JWT_SECRET_KEY', 'NOT SET')))"
```

**Note the different env var names** — DPAH uses `JWT_SECRET`, agentic dashboard uses `JWT_SECRET_KEY`. Both must have the same value. Also verify both use the same algorithm (`HS256`).

